name: Clusters within clusters
description:
This image, from the NASA/ESA Hubble Space Telescope’s Advanced Camera for Surveys (ACS), reveals thousands of globular clusters lying at the core of a galaxy cluster. 

Name:	Coma Cluster
Type:	Local Universe : Star : Grouping : Cluster : Globular
Local Universe : Galaxy : Grouping : Cluster
Distance:	300 million light years
Constellation:	Coma Berenices
Category:	Galaxies Star Clusters

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.

Credit: ESA/Hubble/NASA
